            </choice>||<!-- 
v2d FN.: "It is also possible to read as satputreṇāvyavasthitāM" 
--><!-- 
BD: Indeed, the two seem equally plausible in the rubbing. I suggest marking this up as an ambiguous reading, preferably with the whole of ānya-saṁsthitāM/āvyavasthitām in it. 
--></l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="3">
          <l n="a">bhraṣṭām ākr̥ṣya rājarddhiṁ</l>
          <l n="b"><lb n="4"/>śūnyām āvāsya puṣkarīM</l>
