          <l n="d">rājñā śrī<unclear>skandava</unclear>
<lb break="no" n="6"/>rmmaṇā||</l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="5">
          <l n="a">pūjārtham asya caiveha</l>
          <l n="b">sodakam bhūri-dakṣiṇaM</l>
          <l n="c">puruṣāya puraṁ <unclear>da</unclear><seg met="+">
              <gap quantity="1" reason="illegible" unit="character"/>
            </seg></l>
          <l n="d"><seg met="====">
              <gap quantity="4" reason="illegible" unit="character"/>
            </seg><!-- 
Editor's conjecture: ttam| atrācandrā 
--><!-- 
BD: This is messy. 1. Yes, gaps in metrical verse should always be represented with metrical pattern (in SUPPLIED tags). 2. Supplied text CANNOT be used as an alternative to sic in a choice element. sic only pairs with corr in choice. 3. The supplied text CANNOT contain </l><l>, this would be an overlap. If such a thing were necessary (but it is not, here), then you would need to close the supplied tag, then close the structural tag and open a new one, then open another supplied tag. 4. Since the editor's restoration is conjectural (though plausible), I would just show the gap (with prosody) in the edition, and give the restoration in a comment, as you have done below. 
--><lb break="no" n="7"/>rkka-tārak<choice>
              <sic>ā</sic>
              <corr>a</corr>
            </choice><unclear>M</unclear>||</l>
          <!-- 
